questionText:
Under call-by-reference, what does this pseudocode print?
x = 5; foo(x); print x;
where foo(ref a) { a = a + 10; }

Consider this pseudocode with DYNAMIC scoping:
x = 1;
function f() { print x; }
function g() { x = 2; f(); }
g();
What is printed?

